# Prerequisites

Clone nfp-drv-kmods.  Obtain firmware files.  Create device and firmware
specific config files (scripts will look for them in cfg/ directory).

# Daemon

Link the service file to systemd:

ln -vf nfp-drv-kmods/tools/nti_web/nti-web.service  /etc/systemd/system/nti-web.service

Enable on boot and start:

systemctl enable nti-web.service
systemctl start nti-web.service

Logs can be viewed with journalctl:

journalctl -u nti-web.service -f

# Web

One needs to install apache, or any other Web server to serve contents of
/var/www/html/.

Scripts will generate files in /var/www/html/gen/.  It's recommended to
create a redirection from /var/www/html/index.html, like this:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="refresh"  content="0; url=gen/tests_displayer.html">
  </head>
  <body> </body>
</html>

gen/tests_displayer.html is the main file.

Log files are compressed with Gzip, HTTP server has to be able to serve
those, for apache add:

<Directory /var/www/html/gen>
  AddEncoding gzip gz
  ForceType text/html
</Directory>
